{{Year in Sri Lanka|1987}}

The following lists events that happened during '''[[1987]] in [[Sri Lanka]]'''.

==Incumbents==
*[[President of Sri Lanka|President]]: [[J. R. Jayewardene]]

==Events==
* The [[Indo-Sri Lanka Peace Accord]] was signed in Colombo on 29 July 1987, between Indian Prime Minister Rajiv Gandhi and Sri Lankan President J. R. Jayewardene.<ref name=iclq>[http://journals.cambridge.org/abstract_S0020589300047734 M. L. Marasinghe (1988). Ethnic Politics and Constitutional Reform: The Indo-Sri Lankan Accord. International and Comparative Law Quarterly, 37, pp 551–587 ] {{doi|10.1093/iclqaj/37.3.551}}</ref>
* Civil war rages in the north between the LTTE and the government.
* In June 1987, the [[Sri Lankan Army]] besieged the town Jaffna, civilian casualties began to mount.<ref name=NYT>[https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?sec=health&res=9B0DE0D8173FF936A35755C0A961948260&n=Top%2fNews%2fWorld%2fCountries%20and%20Territories%2fIndia India Airlifts Aid to Tamil Rebels"], ''[[The New York Times]]''. 5 June 1987</ref>

