{{Year in Sri Lanka|1995}}

The following lists events that happened during '''[[1995]] in [[Sri Lanka]]'''.

==Incumbents==
*[[President of Sri Lanka|President]]: [[Chandrika Kumaratunga]] 

==Events==
*On 25 May 1995, the [[Kallarawa massacre]] was carried out by the [[Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam|LTTE]], killing 42 [[Sinhalese people|Sinhalese]] civilians after LTTE cadres stormed the area. <ref name="The Sunday Times1">[http://sundaytimes.lk/981004/news2.html ''The Sunday Times'', Lighting a candle in the storm.]</ref>
*On 22 September 1995, the [[Sri Lankan Air Force]] [[Nagerkovil school bombing|bombed]] the [[Nagar Kovil Maha Vidyalayam school]] in [[Jaffna]], resulting in the deaths of roughly 34-71 Sri Lankan Tamil civilians based on multiple accounts. <ref name="HRW">{{cite web |url=https://www.hrw.org/reports/1996/WR96/Asia-08.htm|title=Human Rights Development - Sri Lanka|accessdate=2006-01-11 |work=HRW }}</ref>
